com.worksap.nlp.sudachi

インタフェース Lattice


  • public interface Lattice
    A graph structure used in the morphological analysis.

    A node of the graph is a morpheme and has a position of the input text. Only the adjacent nodes are connected.

    関連項目:
    LatticeNode

    • メソッドの詳細

      • getNodesWithEnd

        java.util.List<? extends LatticeNode> getNodesWithEnd(int end)
        Returns the nodes which ends at the specified index.

        The last position of the nodes is end - 1.

        パラメータ:
        end - the index to after the last position in the input text
        戻り値:
        the list of nodes which end at end or an empty list if there is no node

      • getNodes

        java.util.List<? extends LatticeNode> getNodes(int begin,
                                               int end)
        Returns the nodes at the specified index.

        The range of nodes begins at the specified begin and extends to the end - 1.

        パラメータ:
        begin - the index to the first position in the input text
        end - the index to after the last position in the input text
        戻り値:
        the list of nodes which start at begin and end at end or an empty list if there is no node

      • getMinimumNode

        java.util.Optional<? extends LatticeNode> getMinimumNode(int begin,
                                                         int end)
        Returns the node has the minimum cost at the specified index.

        The range of the node begins at the specified begin and extends to the end - 1.

        パラメータ:
        begin - the index to the first position in the input text
        end - the index to after the last position in the input text
        戻り値:
        the node which start at begin and end at end

      • insert

        void insert(int begin,
            int end,
            LatticeNode node)
        Insert the node at the specified index.

        The range of the node begins at the specified begin and extends to the end - 1.

        パラメータ:
        begin - the index to the first position in the input text
        end - the index to after the last position in the input text
        node - the node to be inserted

      • remove

        void remove(int begin,
            int end,
            LatticeNode node)
        Remove the node at the specified index.

        The range of the node begins at the specified begin and extends to the end - 1.

        If the node does not exist at the specified position, this method do nothing.

        パラメータ:
        begin - the index to the first position in the input text
        end - the index to after the last position in the input text
        node - the node to be removed

      • createNode

        LatticeNode createNode()
        Allocate a new node.
        戻り値:
        a new node has no information
